data %>% dplyr::count(idCountry) %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x=reorder(idCountry,n), y=n)) + 
  geom_bar(stat="identity", position=position_dodge())+
  ggtitle("Bases de Datos por Pas") +
  scale_fill_brewer(palette="Paired") +
  coord_flip()+
  theme_minimal() + xlab("Nmero de Bases de Datos") + 
  ylab("Pas")

data %>% dplyr::count(gYear) %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x=gYear, y=n)) + 
  geom_point(color = "steelblue")+
  scale_fill_brewer(palette="Paired") +
  theme_minimal() +
  ggtitle("Nmero de Bases de Datos por Ao") + 
  xlab("Aos") + 
  ylab("Nmero de Bases de Datos")

tmp <- data %>% group_by(idCountry) %>% 
    mutate(countT= n()) %>%
    group_by(gYear, add=TRUE) %>%
    dplyr::summarize(n = n(),
                     countT = min(countT)) %>% 
  mutate(pecentage=round(100*n/countT,2))

tmp %>% ggplot() + geom_bar(aes(y = pecentage, x = idCountry,
                                      fill = as_factor(gYear)),stat="identity") +
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 90, hjust = 1))+ 
  ggtitle("Porcentaje de Bases de Datos por Ao - Pas") + 
  xlab("Pas") + 
  ylab("Porcentaje")
